      "message": "Just curious about the \"no packed\" structs. Are we not dealing with serialised data on libpldm? Indeed, there are other packed structs on the same header - will they also be deprecated? Is the idea that encode/decode functions will take all data as arguments? Because I\u0027m imagining that \"packing/unpacking\" data from non-packed structs to the serialised bytes will use some processing that would be \"free\" for the packed case (well, accessing them on the packed structs would have its own costs - are these big enough to justify the extra work on serialisation?).",
